+{"id":"bd-1vr1","title":"Test coverage + e2e logging overhaul","description":"Goal: reach near-complete unit test coverage without mocks/fakes and add fully instrumented E2E integration suites with rich logging/diagnostics. This epic breaks down the work into baseline audits, harness/infra, mock-to-real conversions, and detailed E2E scenarios. Constraints: avoid mock.module()/mock data paths unless truly unavoidable; prefer real DBs, real services, and real CLI tooling. Success: unit tests exercise real code paths with integration-grade fixtures; E2E tests capture console/network/ws logs, traces, screenshots, and timing metadata for every scenario.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:25:28.297032911Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:25:28.297032911Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.1","title":"Baseline unit coverage + gap map (gateway/web/packages)","description":"Run bun test --coverage (and any package-level coverage tools) for apps/gateway, apps/web, and packages/* to establish current statement/branch/line/function coverage. Capture per-module gaps and hotspots (0% coverage files, critical services, WS hub, driver registry, etc.). Produce a concise baseline report (where results live, how to regenerate). Success: reproducible coverage commands + explicit list of uncovered modules.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:07.875242007Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:07.875242007Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:07.875242007Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.10","title":"E2E runner scripts: boot gateway+web with seeded DB","description":"Create a deterministic E2E runner that starts the gateway and web apps, seeds a fresh sqlite DB, exposes health checks, and tears down cleanly. Provide a single command for CI/local to run Playwright against a known-good environment. Success: E2E tests always run against a real backend with predictable data and no mock mode.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:28:03.478103732Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:28:03.478103732Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.10","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:28:03.478103732Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.2","title":"Inventory mocks/fakes + elimination plan","description":"Scan test suites for mock.module, mock data toggles, stubbed runners, and fake network responses (gateway + web + tests/e2e). Classify each usage by feasibility to replace with real integration (real DB, real CLI, real WS). Produce a conversion plan listing exact test files and proposed real fixtures. Success: documented inventory + clear replacement path for each mock.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:17.511605131Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:17.511605131Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:17.511605131Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.3","title":"Build real DB + service test harness","description":"Create a shared test harness that boots the gateway with a real sqlite DB (temp path per test run), runs migrations, and exposes helpers for seeding accounts/agents/alerts/etc. Ensure WAL + cleanup are deterministic. Provide utilities to spin up/tear down the Bun server and WebSocket hub for integration tests. Success: tests can run against real services without mocks.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:30.022568928Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:30.022568928Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:30.022568928Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.4","title":"Deterministic runtime controls for tests","description":"Standardize time/UUID/random controls so tests can assert exact outputs without mocks. Provide utilities for fixed timestamps, seeded randomness, and deterministic IDs where needed (ideally via config injection, not mock.module). Success: flaky timing eliminated and integration tests can rely on reproducible state.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:41.481131212Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:41.481131212Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:41.481131212Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.5","title":"Playwright logging + diagnostics framework","description":"Add a shared E2E logging framework: capture browser console/error events, network request/response summaries, WebSocket messages, and timing metrics; enable trace/video/screenshot artifacts on failure; and emit a structured run log per test. Update Playwright config/reporters accordingly. Success: every E2E test yields a deterministic log bundle usable for debugging.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:52.579658560Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:52.579658560Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:52.579658560Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.6","title":"Gateway tests: remove mock.module in setup-readiness/agent-detection","description":"Replace mock.module usage in setup readiness/detection tests (e.g., apps/gateway/src/__tests__/setup-readiness.test.ts) with real detection flows driven by actual CLI presence or controlled test fixtures on PATH. Use the real DB harness and avoid module-level mocks; provide deterministic inputs via temp filesystem and env config. Success: these tests run without bun:test mocks and validate real detection logic.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:22.825090055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:22.825090055Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:22.825090055Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.7","title":"Gateway unit tests: service layer real DB/WS (no mocks)","description":"Expand/convert service-layer tests (agent, reservation, dcg, safety, handoff, history, metrics, notifications) to run against the real sqlite DB + in-process hub rather than mocked modules. Use the shared harness for setup/teardown and deterministic runtime controls. Success: core services are exercised end-to-end in unit scope with zero mock.module usage.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:32.865277725Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:32.865277725Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.7","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:32.865277725Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.8","title":"Web unit tests: disable mock mode + use real API fixtures","description":"Ensure web unit tests run with mockMode=false and rely on real API fixtures from a test gateway instance (or deterministic seeded data). Replace any test assumptions that depend on mock data with real responses. Validate hooks (useSnapshot/useSafetyPosture/useVelocity) against live endpoints. Success: component/hook tests exercise real data flow rather than mock data branches.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:42.610726175Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:42.610726175Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.8","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:42.610726175Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"bd-1vr1.9","title":"Packages unit tests: agent-drivers + flywheel-clients without mocks","description":"Increase coverage in packages/agent-drivers and packages/flywheel-clients by exercising real command runners, file IO, and protocol parsing. Avoid mock.module and prefer temporary directories + real subprocess execution where feasible. Add integration tests for driver selection, capability detection, and client error handling. Success: package-level coverage is materially improved without fake drivers or mocked modules.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:53.224936354Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:53.224936354Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.9","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:53.224936354Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
